Subject: Re: [VB] WCM mis-representation

I bought a rubber seal for the vent flap a week ago, WCM product, it
also had no rivets despite bearing the same part number as the one in
their catalogue which said 14 rivets included! So I used a pop rivet
gun and the job was done pretty quick. I am just glad they make the
seal, because if I had to make it myself I doubt I would have got
around to doing it yet. And the new seal really helps keep heat in,
rain out, to me it is worth however much I overpaid for a piece of
rubber.
Thanks to your post I won't waste my money on 211-810, so that's a
tiny blow to them.

